content.detailedDescription:
I was driving alone south on groesbeck in warren, mi. right before the 9 mile and groesbeck stop light, i saw a large chrome spacecraft because the sun reflected off of it. you couldn't miss it. it seemed to be a couple miles away maybe south. i stared at it for maybe 30 seconds at the red light. it wasn't moving. it seemed way larger than a passenger aircraft and definitely not a helicopter. i grabbed my phone to get proof. it disappeared. like it just became the same color of the sky since it wasn't moving. i glanced at the car clock 7:12 pm. 

i live not far from where i've seen it. 13 months ago there was another incident at my house, that involved a mysterious blue light. 

this is the complete truth. i am just disappointed that i couldn't get a pic.
content.summary: Large bright chrome unknown object in middle of the b;ue sky

content.detailedDescription: I was at home watching tv when i noticed how bright and full the moon looked. i got up and looked out my patio doors to get a better look at the moon. i suddenly noticed a bright white orb to the right of the moon. it briefly hovered there then it seemed to move slowly beneath the moon. i ran and grabbed my ipad, threw the doors open and stepped outside onto my patio step, and started taking pictures as quickly as i could. the orb silently went from the right side of the moon to the left side but seemed like it was beneath the moon all the while it was moving as in an arc. it suddenly disappeared as though someone turned off a light. i previously witnessed a bunch of red glowing orbs pass over the park behind my home, but this was the first time i saw the white glowing orb. i am always amazed by brilliant stars and moving heavenly objects! could it have been another planet? i suppose anything is possible, but i don't believe this was the case because it was in my view so briefly and moved right to left before disappearing from sight suddenly. i had forgotten about these pictures i took until recently when i was putting pictures into albums. the only reason i know the date i took these photos is because my ipad placed my photos under the date taken. i believe the timeline would be between 8:00 and 10:00 p.M. hope this helps!
content.summary: I noticed a bright orb in the sky while observing the full moon. i took pictures with ipad and shortly after orb disappeared.

content.detailedDescription:
I was a passenger in a convertible. we were waiting at a light to turn left. i noticed two gold spheres in the air. one was getting closer to the other. i made not of how high the one sphere was vs. the one approaching using marking on a telephone pole because i'm a giant aviation nerd and thought i might be witnessing what was about to be a mid air collision. 

the way the one craft (i assumed helicopter) was approaching the second didn't make sense based on how helicopters fly so i thought maybe i was seeing the top of a cell tower and that as we turned left the change in my prospective was what was causing the two gold spheres to almost intersect. but that didn't make much sense either- and then i noticed another 3 to 4 of the gold spheres scattered from about one hand span to 2 hand spans to the right of the initial 2 gold spheres i noticed.

i was still working under the assumption they were helicopters but the lighting wasn't correct. i assumed that maybe the fog was causing the flashing position lights to be seen as one glowing light. but the light was more like a gold street light color then a bright white led position or landing lights. the way the gold lights were moving also didn't look like any kind of formation or path that a helicopter would or even could take. 

it's a busy air corridor usually with helicopters ferrying people back and forth the the hamptons. i was either too busy looking at the gold lighted flying objects to notice other air traffic or there wasn't much at that time. 

i noticed that the gold sphere objects would change in number but that one seemed to remain constant. there was scattered cloud coverage but in at least one instance of the lighted object disappearing from view, i could see stars behind it. so that leads me to believe that it turned it's lights off and didn't just go behind a cloud. the trailing (from my perspective at least)  other 3 to 5 objects were more intermittent. possibly due to clouds, possibly for other reasons. the objects never seemed to move more than two finger spans and seemed loosely grouped. the entirety of them spanned about  3 handspans of the sky and 1 hand span up and down. 

my reactions was one of confusion because i couldn't make sense out of the formation or characteristics of the objects. lost sight because we were driving and they went behind trees. by the time we pulled over to see better they had disappeared completely but there was also 0 cloud coverage then and all stars were visible. a helicopter went over head then and it was very obviously a helicopter.
content.summary: Multiple gold spheres in the sky varying between 3 and 7

content.detailedDescription: I was putting my kids to bed, then one of my sons insisted that i look through the window. he was saying ,,mommy the ghosts are taking pictures of us!" it was really dark inside their room with no light, curtains were on but some flashes of light brighten the room. i got up and moved the curtains and saw through the window a flaming cross in yellow orange color. part of the night sky was flashing lights without thunder.The same place on the sky where crosses emerged.They were flying like some sort of entity not like vehicle ...  they were headed in our direction so i saw the cross closely. fire was inside of the cross.No shining outside the cross. shape was solid.And transparent ameba shape was behind the cross, i saw that when it gor really close. children got really upset so i was scared and run with them to call my husbend who was sleeping. i woke him up and got him to the window to watch crosses but there was only flaming ball in the sky. flames of fire were also inside,with no shining outside the ball. it was moving strangely and after few moments it disappeared, fly away fast, 5 to 10 minutes everything was back to normal, no flashing in the sky. duration of the event with crosses was about 20 minutes or more...
content.summary: \it was my 4year old son that notice something was strange outside. sky was strange, no rain, no thunder sound just flashing lights...And crosses in flame inside

content.summary: Object observed from i-5 swiftly flying south

content.detailedDescription:
I am writing you about my own sighting (last night) because your organization seems like a logical place to start.

in any case, i was feeding my horses last night - about half way between the towns of monte rio and duncan's mills (west sonoma county, ca). this is away from bright city lights and offers a very good view of the stars at night. at around 9:30 pm, i happened to look up at the hills to the north west (near where the sun had set some minutes earlier), and from this point in the sky, i witnessed 7 individual lights move in from the north west (where the sky was still somewhat lit up from the setting sun), and they moved in right in the sky directly above me.

3 of them were a brilliant green color, 2 of them were an intense cobalt blue, one of them was white, and there was one faint red one... they did not move in a pattern - they were moving randomly...Some circled back and then back again, others just zoomed in and looked as though they coasted to slow stops... they all moved with a fluid motion - the best analogy i can come up with is that they moved like fish in water. they would accelerate effortlessly and then coast for a while before either accelerating again and/or changing directions.

i watched them for at least 10 minutes before some of them simply disappeared and others started moving south east. a few minutes after they were gone, 2 more showed up (coming again from the north west) - a green light and a white light this time. they moved again randomly, but more or less stayed in the same area for several more minutes before they both also started moving to the south east - although the green light moved in directly behind the white one as they departed in what looked like an upwards (away from the earth) and towards the south east direction.
content.flightPath: Path with directional change,Path then hovering
content.summary: Brilliant blue, green, white and red objects moving independently and randomly in sky

content.detailedDescription:
I was with some friends in a farm field to have a party while we watched the rising solstice full moon on june 21, 2106.  

we watched the rising moon and i decided to try and take some pictures of the moon with a large tree in view and a roadway (highway # 313.)  i was trying to capture a cars headlights along this road together with the moon and the large tree.  the only light in my scene was coming from the bright moon.  i made about 15 pictures on my smart phone. i was frustrated because i could get the picture i wanted. 

we each had an adirondack chair to sit on in one row before the rising moon.  a little later from the time i took some smart phone pictures, i saw, what appears to be a flying saucer moving in four different positions in the basic picture i taking from my stationary adirondack chair. 

i have picture files. nobody saw anything like a flying saucer in the sky but they all were shocked to see my files ! i have a few witnesses to my  on the spot files.
content.summary: I was at a solstice party with friends. about 15 of us werew watching a full solstice moom rising over a distant hill with the bright new moon. none of us saw anything except i recorded an apparant saucer in four places.

content.detailedDescription:
I was driving back from the store shortly after 5 pm when i noticed 5 objects in the sky and thought they were party balloons. they were all silver and i swore i saw some string hanging down from one of them. when i got home i looked up at them because they looked like they were going to fly over my house and i love balloons. when i looked for them i noticed 5 white lights instead of balloons. they appeared to be much higher. i didn't see the change because i was driving. they seem to almost twinkle like a star. they appeared to stay in one spot for 3-4 min and there was one that seemed to move independently of the others.  first it was to the right of the other 4 then it moved closer, meanwhile the other 4 stayed together.  during this time a single plane, could have been a private jet flew past them. the plane was on my side like it flew between the lights and myself.   the 5 lights then started moving, like they were drifting on the wind, sort of like balloons. it was a typical sunny arizona day with little to no wind, no clouds. the objects then moved towards the east(ish) and seemed to stop again. i'm not sure how long they were there since i wasn't pay attention to the time. one seemed to move more than the other four and would get closer and farther from them. at one point it almost looked like 3 of them, which tended to stay together went behind a cloud because they got dim and disappeared, and then came back.  i couldn't see any clouds however. then the other two would be gone and came back. it was instantaneous like a light turn off. they always came back in the same location. finally there were only 2 left, they would disappear for a second or two and show back up and then finally were just gone. they really did look like stars. it may have been the sun reflecting off balloons but it definitely struck me as odd. i wasn't scared i just thought huh, i wonder if anyone else saw that.  i took a picture with my phone and a video but you can't see anything, and i can't upload my pictures because there is something screwy with my phone not connecting to the computer. sorry, it sounds like an excuse but it is true. i do still have them on my phone, but all you see is clear blue sky. if there is an email address i can send them to you that way. 
it may very well have been balloons but i wasn't sure if anyone else had reported anything strange. 
thanks.
content.summary: Saw 5 objects in the sky, thought they were 5 party balloons but as they came closer they became more like stars

content.detailedDescription:
i just wanted to write you tonight and let you know of a ufo sighting that happened in niagara falls ontuesday june 12th 2016.

i am a bellman at one of the major hotels right near the falls. during one of my many routine luggage calls yesterday (the day of the event), i happened to look out the window of the 43rd floor while waiting for the elevator.

from this vantage point one can see most of the niagara region and even toronto on the distant shores of lake ontario. this was the direction that i was looking when i noticed two large rectangles that would almost pass for solar panels hovering in the sky.

as i watched them, the alternately bobbed up and down, crossed paths and then slowly drifted apart. i watched them, trying to figure out what they were for a few more minutes before they once again began to drift back together. 

at this point they appeared to be over niagara on the lake, a town about 20 miles kilometres away, and still were very visible in the sky which means they must have been quite big.

i left to go back down to work and informed another bellman to look out the window during his next call. he did so and came back astonished and unable to explain what he saw.

later in the day, a co-worker called us from a different part of the city letting us know he just saw the same ufo and snapped a few pictures of it. i have attached one of the photos below.

a few hours later another co-worker walked into the building exclaiming he saw a ufo while driving to work. when we asked him what he saw he recounted an almost identical report of the objects we had viewed earlier in the day.

this morning i noticed that a report has been created with mufon by a person living in st. catharine's (another near by city) and once again, the report details the exact object that we all witnessed. 

whether it was aliens or a secret government craft i can't be sure. all i know is that i look to the skies every day, seeing helicopters and planes flying over the falls... but i have never, ever seen anything like this before.
content.summary: Rectangle ufo's in niagara falls

content.detailedDescription:
On 19th february 2016 i left home for work as usual at 0518 hours. it was a cold morning with a clear morning sky (i could see the stars). i started to walk south along the road whereby 30 seconds later i noticed three(3) large orange/red coloured spheres in the south sky around 45 degrees up. i noticed the spheres because they were so bright and low in the sky. at first i thought it must be some kind of planetary line up because the three spheres were in a horizontal line and that's what it looked like, but i realised this was ridiculous because i am into amateur astronomy and i was not aware of any such thing taking place. i also ruled out the constellation orion because the constellation was below the horizon that morning. i even opened a app called stellarium on my mobile phone to confirm this. initially the spheres appeared to be stationary for around 8 minutes from my vantage point and i began to take photos using my mobile phone at 0524 hours. when i reached the end of the road i was now looking at the spheres head on where i think i began to notice some kind of movement from one of the spheres. i carried on taking photos whilst walking where i then confirmed that all three spheres were moving in my direction heading north. i crossed the road and started to film the spheres on my mobile phone moving across the sky. i saw a member of the public and pointed the spheres out to him as i wanted another witness to observe them. we both observed the spheres move overhead (at this stage the spheres appeared white in colour and not as large) and at that time one of the spheres began to blink, then followed by the second sphere which also began to blink. all three spheres moved over rooftops in the main road where we both lost sight of them heading north. 

these spheres (lights) were seen by a number of people on their way to work that morning. my brother being one of them who at the time was driving south along the m11 motorway from halstead. i reported the incident to my local paper with the hope that other persons would come forward with what they saw?
content.summary: I left home at 0518 hours for work. within 30 seconds i was looking up at three(3) large orange/red coloured spheres that appeared stationary in the south. it looked like a row of three(3) planets in a line.

content.detailedDescription: While looking out of my bedroom window looking east. i was looking at the calm night sky.  i noticed a airline jet in the south traveling in a east to west direction. a few minutes later another light caught my eye towards the east over prince edward island. the light blinked and reappeared a few degrees northwest of its first sighting.  this continued to dart across the sky at a speed i never witness before.  i could not see the light after the tree line to the north.  if this object was reference to an airliner,  the object flew over prince edward island,  crossing the northumberland strait and into northern new brunswick in a straight flight path that took less than 5 seconds. the light was brighter than a plan and the speed of this object was overwhelming. i am a very sceptical person who wants tangible proof before saying anything.  i have a strong feeling that i had to report this.
content.summary: Incredible fast bright pulsing light that dashed across the sky

content.detailedDescription: I was walking my dog in the front yard. i was hit with a light. it felt like it went down in me, then back up..It felt like it lifted my upper body up just a little bit. i felt expanded. i felt like i was energy and light. when i looked at everything, it was covered in shimmering light. the grass, the leaves, my arms. when i looked around, my movement felt like it was flowing. it stopped after about 10 secs. then for about 20 mins after, i would get a small glimpse of that feeling, and i would get goosebumps up and down my arms, and a warm feeling across my chest. the next morning i noticed a rash starting on my chest and arms. it spread very fast. across my chest, down my shoulders, arms and tops of my hands. everywhere that was exposed the day before. i saw a dr..And a dermotologist. they do not know what it is. they tested for cancer..Negative. they gave me a steroid..Didnt work at all.Nothing will help it. i still have the rash..It wont go away. its itchy, bright red, and is kind of shaped like leopard spots. if im in the sun too long..It puffs up a little. then it goes flat again, but hasnt gone away or gotten any lighter. i have also been hearing things in just my left ear since then. i hear humming, ringing, txt tone sounds, and afew times i have heard people talking..Some in different languages, being changed every couple secs, like channels on a radio station.
content.summary: Did not see the ufo, but was hit with light. i felt different and could see everything covered in light.

content.detailedDescription: I noticed a very bright light in the sky . it would get really bright then it would fade a little thrn again. i said to myself , "that is no star".I decided to take out my phone snap some pictures possibly a video. before my phone i could only see the glowing one . i did not move rapidly. it moved in its own little bubble. it was not flat it looked like if the ship was side ways . hard to explain. before i started recording i took three pictures but didn't check them out right after taking them. i started t record. i zoomed all the way in . i noticed that to the left of the bright object was a weird shape red kind of flare did not move much . at first i tho it was my thumb or something or maybe something stuck to my lense so i cleaned it . the red object was still there . the glowing obect would move in a weird way glow brighter than other times. i recoreded for 18 seconds . 12 seconds through the video my phone froze, but it was still recording for the rest 6 seconds. on its own my phone went back to my homescreen . usually you would get a report statinh camera has stopped working but i got nothing. i tried recording twice again and it would only record for 2 seconds and it would take me out of camera app to my homescreen and it did not let me record. i went back to view the three pictures but there were no pictures in my gallery nor the 2 second videos. the light slowly started going doen and disappeared behind the hills.

content.detailedDescription:
Something traversed between my wife and i about 4 feet off the ground that made an unidentifiable noise and the speed of which was extraordinarily fast. neither of us place any credence in "aliens among us" or visitations...The physics against such things are irrefutable. my career was in astronomy on top of mauna kea in hawaii, my wife was a banker and accountant...

what ever it was created a distortion in the air between us for an instant. we live in a suburban area and our residence is surrounded by a fir forest. to the right of me from whence "it" came is a 150 meter tall hill about 50 meters away which we also own..Aside from the noise of the event there was absolutely no report one might ascribe to the discharge of a fire arm...Our area is for the most part dead quiet. 

if it were a bullet etc. "it" would have to be able to climb a 150 meter tall hill, go over the top then descend to our level and go absolutely parallel to the ground between us. i have been reluctant to "report" this because of my own core beliefs, however one of my friends encouraged me to do so anyway..

i have a home observatory (a meade 12 inch lx200) and do a lot of observing hunting for neos...I have yet to see anything inexplainable either here or on top of mauna kea...Having said that, the event my wife and i witnessed not only frightened us but left us with profound curiosity as to its origin...

the distortion in the air between us looked as if we were looking through water...The noise was subtle but unlike anything we have ever heard.. i own guns and know a ricochet when i hear one...Am i alone in this???
content.summary: Something traversed from my right to left between my wife and i while in our yard...

content.detailedDescription:
I was taking a walk outside and when i looked west i saw a bright object hovering in the sky, in the distance, that wasn't making any sound. it would slightly move every once in a while but didn't seem to be moving away on a path. during this time, it would also slightly fade in brightness and then go back to its regular brightness. 

after a few minutes, it began to travel on a westward path without its brightness varying all that much and then, out of nowhere, the object's light faded out quickly. similar to how a light dimmer looks when it is quickly shut off. the whole event lasted around 15 minutes. less than five minutes later i saw two aircraft to the south of me, one right behind another, also headed westward. photo included is of a rendition of what i saw, made from the street address in google street view.
content.summary: Bright white light hovered, continued on path, then quickly faded out

content.detailedDescription:
At around 10:45 to 10:50 pm last night (7/13/16) i was outside on my patio smoking a cigarette, as usual. now i had seen multiple satellites very high up in the sky before, on a nightly basis. where i live there are very few city lights, and on a clear night everything is very clear. these satellites typically moved from south to north in the sky and appeared star-like. but that is a digression. 
last night: so i looked to the northwest, and saw a large blue light and object, hovering over the trees and apartment complex near the top of the hill (that would be near the intersection of burnham rd. and harrier ave.). previously i'd seen helicopters and conventional aircraft before around here. however they have bright white lights and red flashing lights, and not a large blueish light as i saw last night. there were no other lights as the object approached me. just a very large blue light and outline of the craft. as it approached me, i was pretty scared, and was swearing outside. most of these ufos do not scare me. but this one was odd in its lighting and color. i felt a numbness in my head and was sure i was going to get abducted this time. in fact that happens alot when i see these strange things or look at programs about aliens and alien abduction, aside from missing time. 
as the object approached slowly, and i mean slowly, it was barely moving, it moved slightly to the left and right, then went straight. i was looking at the time on my clock inside, through the window, throughout the event. luckily the time stayed consistent! well then it passed over, and i went outside again. on the underside of the craft, there was a small red and small white light, and some light noise. however nowhere near as loud as a conventional aircraft. 
**previous to the sighting: i was inside on my computer, and felt extremely disoriented. for a second i had little or no idea of where i was, i.E. location, address, state of mind. ** 
***around that time also i heard noises in the backyard (it's a large grassy hillside with a fig tree and other brush to the lefet) and saw a grey flash at the bottom of that yard nearest the bottom fence. *** 

in the past, i have seen ufos in the skies. i have had episodes of missing time too, not attributable to drugs and/or alcohol. but what happened last night concerned me a great deal, and scared me. it seemed to me that the aliens were granting me my wishes, and getting closer. i had asked inwardly for that to happen, to actually see a ship very close to me. so be careful what you wish for!!
content.summary: Strange large blueish light moved very slowly over my hilltop last night!
